  "response": "The highest salary package for a Chemical Engineering graduate after completing an M.Tech in India can vary significantly based on several factors, including the reputation of the institute, the individual's academic performance, relevant work experience, and the hiring company. In premier institutions such as the Indian Institutes of Technology (IITs), graduates may receive packages upwards of INR 20-25 lakhs per annum. Multinational corporations, technological firms, and petrochemical companies often offer competitive salaries that can exceed these figures based on the role and location.",
